in recent years , u.s. steelmakers have supplied about 80 % of the 100 million tons of steel used annually by the nation . of the remaining 20 % needed , the unk negotiations unk about 15 % to foreign suppliers , with the difference supplied mainly by canada -- which is n't included in the quota program . other countries that do n't have formal steel quotas with the u.s. , such as taiwan , sweden and argentina , also have supplied steel . some of these countries have in recent years made informal agreements with the u.s. that are similar to quotas .
