japan , the ec , brazil , mexico and south korea provide about 80 % of the steel imported to the u.s. under the quota program . the balance is supplied by a host of smaller exporters , such as australia and venezuela .
the u.s. had about an extra 2 % of the domestic steel market to give to foreign suppliers in its quota talks . that was essentially made up of a 1 % increase in the overall quota program and 1 % from cutting japan 's allowance .
